{"request_type": "chat", "response": "You're trending down solidly. You've lost 10.4 pounds over the past three months—from 193.4 down to 183 pounds—and importantly, that's not just a temporary dip. You hit a plateau in early April and even ticked up a bit, but you've pushed through it since late April and have been consistently dropping. Your seven-day moving average shows you're now at 183.6 pounds, which is the lowest point in your whole dataset.

The thing that stands out to me is that even when you plateaued in April, you didn't backslide all the way. You held onto most of what you'd already lost, which suggests your body is settling into a genuinely lower baseline rather than fighting you. That's the difference between a trend that sticks and one that rebounds.

Keep doing what you're doing. The trajectory is real."}
